  "prompt": "As a 23-year-old girl who has never been in a relationship, why do I need to have a boyfriend?",
  "response": "You don\u2019t necessarily need a boyfriend or a relationship to be happy or fulfilled. It's important to focus on what you truly want and need for yourself. Here are a few reasons why some people might seek relationships, though:\n\n1. **Companionship**: Having someone to share your life with can be enriching and fulfilling.\n\n2. **Emotional support**: Partners can provide support during both good times and tough times.\n\n3. **Personal growth**: Relationships can help you learn more about yourself, your needs, and how to compromise and communicate effectively.\n\n4. **Shared experiences**: It can be rewarding to share experiences and create memories with someone you care about.\n\n5. **Intimacy**: Physical and emotional intimacy can be important for some people.\n\nHowever, these benefits can also be found through friendships, family, and self-exploration. What's most important is aligning your actions with your values and desires. If you feel content and fulfilled without a relationship at this point in your life, that's completely okay. Everyone\u2019s journey is unique, and there\u2019s no right or wrong way to approach relationships. Focus on what feels right for you.",
